2021 KCSE exam English paper exam [Robert Menza, Standard]  Four university students arrested in connection with the leakage of the Kenya Certificate of Secondary Education examination were arraigned yesterday.  messrs James Sum Obongo, Justus Kimurgor Leting and Kelvin Kiprotich Langat from Rongo University College and Gideon Kibet Tonui of Baringo Technical University appeared before Milimani Senior Principal Magistrate Robinson Ondiek.  They were charged with being in possession of Kenya National Examination Council content for the 2021 KCSE examination in their mobile phones between March 15 and 18.  They denied the charges and were released on a bond of Sh500,000 or alternatively pay a cash bail of Sh300,000.   By Moses Nyamori | 1 day ago By Collins Kweyu | 2 days ago By Gitau Wanyoike | 2 days ago By Betty Njeru | 3 days ago